Setup Java in Visual Studio Code, assuming we have a Visual Studio Code already. 
If you don't have it yet, follow the instructions here to install: https://github.com/mfulo/install/blob/b7fec79e6614e29d91d7766bd5763afef3605110/visualStudioCode

Check if you have java
- Check first if you have java installed in your computer
- Open your cmd
- Type "java -version"
- If the message goes like this: 
    'java' is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file.
  then you don't have java

Download java
- Go to https://code.visualstudio.com/
- Click "Download for Windows" but don't save the application
- Click "Java" on the left pane
- Select "Getting Started"
- Under "Setting up VS Code for Java Development" section, click the "Install the Coding Pack for Java - Windows"
- Double click on the downloaded exe file
- Accept agreement >> Next >> Install

Check if you now have java
- Repeat the process with cmd
- Check it with VS code too
 
